    feat: add FAB-integrated music player with unified control panel
    
    Introduce a new FAB entry mode for the music player that integrates
    seamlessly with the existing floating action button group (TOC, BackToHome,
    BackToTop). The music player now has two display modes:
    
    - 'default': original floating orb/mini-player with standalone floating
      playlist panel
    - 'fab': simplified FAB-style entry button that opens a compact control
      panel styled after the sidebar music widget
    
    Key changes:
    - Add floatingEntryMode config (default | fab) to MusicPlayerConfig
    - Add MusicFabButton: minimal FAB button showing music icon with playing
      state indicator (green dot + pulse ring when active)
    - Add FabMusicPanel: compact card UI reusing SidebarCover,
      SidebarTrackInfo, SidebarProgress, SidebarControls, and
      SidebarPlaylist components from the sidebar music widget
    - Replace old PlayerBar+Playlist floating layout with the new
      FabMusicPanel in FAB mode, eliminating cross-origin positioning issues
    - Add visible-count-aware positioning so the FAB panel always anchors
      above the full FAB group regardless of how many buttons are visible
    - Freeze FAB button visibility while music panel is expanded to prevent
      layout thrashing during scroll
    - Add light-mode border (rgba(148,163,184,0.45)) to FloatingButton
      and MusicFabButton for consistent visibility on light backgrounds
    - Refactor FloatingControls as a unified FAB group container with
      CSS-variable-driven positioning and responsive breakpoints
    - Add graceful handling of mermaid:render events to avoid FAB layout
      updates during heavy Mermaid rendering sessions
    
    Config change: musicPlayerConfig.floatingEntryMode defaults to 'fab'

